ecov upload; artifact `go-coverage` | `CODECOV_TOKEN` passed to Codecov action when present | `secrets.CODECOV_TOKEN` (optional; declared for `workflow_call`) |\n| `codegen-check.yml` | Codegen Check | `pull_request` â†’ `main`, `release-*` | `codegen`: `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile` | `codegen-check` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24.4; `make gen-check` | â€” | â€” |\n| `copyright-check.yml` | Copyright Check | `pull_request` â†’ `main`, `release-*` | `copyright`: all files except `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**` | `build` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: `apt install moreutils`; `make gen-copyright`; `git diff --exit-code` | â€” | â€” |\n| `codespell.yml` | Codespell | `pull_request` â†’ `main`, `release-*` | *(none â€” scans tree after temporarily removing some manifests)* | `codespell` | Backup/remove `pyproject.toml`, `package.json`, `package-lock.json`; `pip install codespell`; `codespell` with `--check-filenames`, `--skip`, `--ignore-words-list`; restore files | â€” | â€” |\n| `build-push-release.yml` | Build and Push Release Images | `push` â†’ `main`; `push` tags `v*.*.*`, `v*.*.*-*` | *(none)* | `build-and-push` | Checkout; Go 1.24.4; Buildx; `docker/login-action` to `ghcr.io`; set `TAG` from ref; `make docker-buildx-push` (workload manager), `docker-buildx-push-router`, `docker-buildx-push-picod` with `IMAGE_REGISTRY` | `TAG`, `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}` | `GITHUB_TOKEN` (registry login) |\n| `dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Dify Plugin Publish | `push` tags `dify-plugin/v*` | *(none)* | `publish` | Download `dify-plugin` CLI 0.0.6; install `yq`; read `manifest.yaml`; package plugin; checkout `author/dify-plugins` with token; move `.difypkg`; branch, commit, push; `gh pr create` to `langgenius/dify-plugins` | `GH_TOKEN` on PR step | `PLUGIN_ACTION` (repo checkout + `gh`; cross-repo PR) |\n| `workflows-approve.yml` | Approve Workflows | `pull_request_target` types `labeled`, `synchronize` â†’ `main`, `release-**` | *(logic: first-time contributor vs `ok-to-test` label)* | `approve` | `github-script`: list contributor PRs; if not first-time or has `ok-to-test`, list `action_required` workflow runs for SHA and approve | â€” | `GITHUB_TOKEN` |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/ci-cd/design.md","time":{"start":1775876794599,"end":1775876794621}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775876794655,"sessionID":"ses_2857ec447ffeq08FwzYRVyueq8","part":{"id":"prt_d7a8168ff001al4yK8tz2sdcdd","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7a8151fc001jHKcE60pWDPOQF","sessionID":"ses_2857ec447ffeq08FwzYRVyueq8","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":19882,"input":4941,"output":99,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":14842}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775876796973,"sessionID":"ses_2857ec447ffeq08FwzYRVyueq8","part":{"id":"prt_d7a81722b00139RVuNvuJcaejr","messageID":"msg_d7a816932001YdZJjwdBjLLx76","sessionID":"ses_2857ec447ffeq08FwzYRVyueq8","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876799389,"sessionID":"ses_2857ec447ffeq08FwzYRVyueq8","part":{"id":"prt_d7a817574001HvyUPpRjbIjlPT","messageID":"msg_d7a816932001YdZJjwdBjLLx76","sessionID":"ses_2857ec447ffeq08FwzYRVyueq8","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_b2869d47d235438f88c3bb43","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-034: CI/CD GitHub Actions\n2: \n3: ## Summary\n4: \n5: Implement comprehensive GitHub Actions CI/CD infrastructure for the AgentCube project, consisting of 12 automated workflows covering build verification, linting, testing, code generation, end-to-end testing, release automation, and contributor workflow approvals.\n6: \n7: ## Purpose\n8: \n9: ### Background\n10: \n11: The AgentCube project requires robust CI/CD automation to ensure code quality, catch regressions early, and automate release processes. The project consists of multiple components:\n12: \n13: - **Go-based Workload Manager** (`workload-manager`)\n14: - **Go-based AgentD Controller** (`agentd`)\n15: - **Python SDK** (`sdk-python`)\n16: - **Kubernetes manifests and Helm charts**\n17: \n18: The current manual build and test processes need automation through GitHub Actions to support:\n19: 1. Pull request validation on multiple code paths\n20: 2. Multi-architecture Docker image building and publishing\n21: 3. End-to-end testing in Kind clusters\n22: 4. Release automation with semantic versioning\n23: 5. Code quality enforcement (linting, spelling, copyright headers)\n24: \n25: ### Goal\n26: \n27: Implement 12 GitHub Actions workflows in `.github/workflows/` that:\n28: \n29: - Run on pull requests to `main` and `release-*` branches\n30: - Use path filtering to avoid unnecessary runs\n31: - Build and push Docker images to GitHub Container Registry\n32: - Run Go and Python tests with coverage reporting\n33: - Perform code generation drift checks\n34: - Execute end-to-end tests on Kind clusters\n35: - Enforce spelling and copyright compliance\n36: - Automate plugin publishing and workflow approvals\n37: \n38: ### Value\n39: \n40: | Benefit | Description |\n41: |---------|-------------|\n42: | **Automation** | Eliminates manual build/test/release steps |\n43: | **Consistency** | Ensures all PRs pass identical checks |\n44: | **Speed** | Path filtering skips irrelevant workflows |\n45: | **Reliability** | E2E tests catch integration issues |\n46: | **Release Efficiency** | Automated image publishing on tags |\n47: | **Quality** | Lint, spelling, copyright enforcement |\n48: \n49: ---\n50: \n51: ## Scope\n52: \n53: ### In-Scope\n54: \n55: | Workflow | Path | Description |\n56: |----------|------|-------------|\n57: | Agentcube CI Workflow | `.github/workflows/main.yml` | Docker build on PR |\n58: | Lint | `.github/workflows/lint.yml` | Go lint with golangci-lint |\n59: | Codegen Check | `.github/workflows/codegen-check.yml` | Verify generated code up-to-date |\n60: | Test Coverage | `.github/workflows/test-coverage.yml` | Go test with coverage |\n61: | E2E Tests | `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` | End-to-end testing on Kind |\n62: | Python SDK Tests | `.github/workflows/python-sdk-tests.yml` | Python SDK unit tests |\n63: | Python Lint | `.github/workflows/python-lint.yml` | Ruff Python linting |\n64: | Codespell | `.github/workflows/codespell.yml` | Spelling check |\n65: | Copyright Check | `.github/workflows/copyright-check.yml` | Copyright header enforcement |\n66: | Build and Push Release Images | `.github/workflows/build-push-release.yml` | Multi-arch image publishing |\n67: | Dify Plugin Publish | `.github/workflows/dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Plugin release automation |\n68: | Approve Workflows | `.github/workflows/workflows-approve.yml` | First-time contributor approval |\n69: \n70: ### Out-of-Scope\n71: \n72: - Jenkins or other CI systems\n73: - Cloud-specific deployments (AWS, GCP)\n74: - Custom GitHub runners\n75: - Performance benchmarking CI\n76: - Security scanning (Dependabot covers dependencies)\n77: \n78: ---\n79: \n80: ## Impact Analysis\n81: \n82: ### Dependencies\n83: \n84: | Dependency | Purpose | Status |\n85: |------------|---------|--------|\n86: | `docker/setup-buildx-action` | Docker buildx setup | Required |\n87: | `docker/login-action` | GHCR login | Required for releases |\n88: | `actions/checkout` | Repository checkout | Required |\n89: | `actions/setup-go` | Go environment | Required |\n90: | `actions/setup-python` | Python environment | Required for Python workflows |\n91: | `helm/kind-action` | Kind cluster creation | Required for E2E |\n92: | `dorny/paths-filter` | Path-based filtering | Required |\n93: | `codecov/codecov-action` | Coverage upload | Optional |\n94: | `aws-actions/configure-aws-credentials` | AWS ECR (future) | Not in initial scope |\n95: | `docker/build-push-action` | Multi-platform builds | Required |\n96: \n97: ### Upstream\n98: \n99: - `ci-cd/spec.md` â€” Requirements document\n100: - `ci-cd/design.md` â€” Technical design specifications\n101: - `Makefile` â€” Build targets referenced by workflows\n102: \n103: ### Downstream Consumers\n104: \n105: 1. **Contributors** â€” All PRs trigger workflow runs\n106: 2. **Release managers** â€” Tag pushes trigger image publishing\n107: 3. **End users** â€” Benefit from tested releases\n108: 4. **External plugins** â€” Dify plugin publishing workflow\n109: \n110: ### Risks\n111: \n112: | Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n113: |------|----------|------------|\n114: | Workflow run timeouts | Medium | Path filtering reduces unnecessary runs; separate jobs |\n115: | Flaky E2E tests | Medium | Artifact collection on failure; retry logic |\n116: | Concurrent workflow limits | Low | Queue management; prioritize main branch |\n117: | Secret exposure | High | Use GitHub secrets; minimize secret usage |\n118: | Dependabot workflow changes | Low | Pin action versions; review updates |\n119: \n120: ---\n121: \n122: ## Alternatives Considered\n123: \n124: ### Option 1: Single monolithic workflow (Not Selected)\n125: \n126: **Pros**: Single trigger, simpler structure\n127: **Cons**: No parallel execution; path filtering not granular; harder to debug\n128: \n129: ### Option 2: CircleCI or Jenkins (Not Selected)\n130: \n131: **Pros**: Mature platforms\n132: **Cons**: Vendor lock-in; requires infrastructure; inconsistent with GitHub ecosystem\n133: \n134: ### Option 3: GitLab CI (Not Selected)\n135: \n136: **Pros**: Built-in Auto DevOps\n137: **Cons**: Project not on GitLab; additional platform to maintain\n138: \n139: ### Option 4: 12 separate workflow files (Selected)\n140: \n141: **Pros**: Fine-grained path filtering; parallel execution; clear separation of concerns; each workflow can be debugged independently\n142: **Cons**: More files to maintain; shared conventions require discipline\n143: \n144: ---\n145: \n146: ## Technical Design\n147: \n148: ### Workflow Summary\n149: \n150: | # | Filename | Trigger | Path Filter | Key Jobs |\n151: |---|----------|---------|-------------|----------|\n152: | 1 | `main.yml` | PR: main, release-* | (none) | build |\n153: | 2 | `lint.yml` | PR: main, release-* | `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `.golangci.yml` | golangci |\n154: | 3 | `codegen-check.yml` | PR: main, release-* | `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile` | codegen-check |\n155: | 4 | `test-coverage.yml` | PR, merge_group, workflow_call | `**` minus md/svg/png/docs | coverage |\n156: | 5 | `e2e.yml` | PR: main, release-* | (none) | e2e-test |\n157: | 6 | `python-sdk-tests.yml` | PR, merge_group | `sdk-python/**` | python-sdk-tests |\n158: | 7 | `python-lint.yml` | PR: main, release-* | `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `pyproject.toml` | python_lint |\n159: | 8 | `codespell.yml` | PR: main, release-* | (none) | codespell |\n160: | 9 | `copyright-check.yml` | PR: main, release-* | copyright: all except md/svg/png/docs/.github | build |\n161: | 10 | `build-push-release.yml` | push: main, tags v*.*.* | (none) | build-and-push |\n162: | 11 | `dify-plugin-publish.yml` | push: tags dify-plugin/v* | (none) | publish |\n163: | 12 | `workflows-approve.yml` | PR: main, release-** | (logic-based) | approve |\n164: \n165: ### Trigger Details\n166: \n167: **Pull Request Triggers:**\n168: - `main` branch â€” primary development branch\n169: - `release-*` pattern â€” release branches\n170: \n171: **Push Triggers:**\n172: - `main` branch â€” for latest image builds\n173: - Semantic version tags: `v*.*.*`, `v*.*.*-*` (e.g., `v1.2.3`, `v1.2.3-beta`)\n174: - Dify plugin tags: `dify-plugin/v*`\n175: \n176: ### Path Filters\n177: \n178: Uses `dorny/paths-filter` for efficient workflow triggering:\n179: \n180: | Filter Name | Patterns |\n181: |-------------|----------|\n182: | lint | `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, `.github/workflows/lint.yml` |\n183: | codegen | `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile` |\n184: | coverage | `**` (all) minus `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**` |\n185: | copyright | All except `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**` |\n186: | python | `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml` |\n187: | sdk | `sdk-python/**` |\n188: \n189: ### Environment Variables\n190: \n191: | Workflow | Variable | Value |\n192: |----------|----------|-------|\n193: | E2E | `ARTIFACTS_PATH` | `${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs` |\n194: | Release | `TAG` | `github.ref_name` (tag) or `latest` |\n195: | Release | `IMAGE_REGISTRY` | `ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}` |\n196: \n197: ### Secrets Required\n198: \n199: | Secret | Purpose | Workflows |\n200: |--------|---------|------------|\n201: | `GITHUB_TOKEN` | GHCR login, workflow approval | build-push-release, workflows-approve |\n202: | `CODECOV_TOKEN` | Coverage upload (optional) | test-coverage |\n203: | `GH_TOKEN` | Cross-repo plugin PR | dify-plugin-publish |\n204: \n205: ### Key Make Targets\n206: \n207: | Target | Workflow | Purpose |\n208: |--------|----------|---------|\n209: | `docker-build` | main.yml | Build workload manager image |\n210: | `docker-build-router` | e2e.yml | Build router image |\n211: | `docker-build-picod` | e2e.yml | Build picod image |\n212: | `docker-buildx-push` | build-push-release.yml | Push workload manager |\n213: | `docker-buildx-push-router` | build-push-release.yml | Push router image |\n214: | `docker-buildx-push-picod` | build-push-release.yml | Push picod image |\n215: | `lint` | lint.yml | Run golangci-lint |\n216: | `gen-check` | codegen-check.yml | Verify code generation |\n217: | `gen-copyright` | copyright-check.yml | Generate copyright headers |\n218: | `e2e` | e2e.yml | Run E2E tests |\n219: | `e2e-clean` | e2e.yml | Cleanup Kind cluster |\n220: \n221: ### Go Version Matrix\n222: \n223: | Workflow | Go Version |\n224: |----------|-------------|\n225: | lint.yml | 1.24 |\n226: | codegen-check.yml | 1.24.4 |\n227: | test-coverage.yml | 1.24 |\n228: | e2e.yml | 1.23 |\n229: | build-push-release.yml | 1.24.4 |\n230: \n231: ### Python Version Matrix\n232: \n233: | Workflow | Python Version |\n234: |----------|----------------|\n235: | python-sdk-tests.yml | 3.12 |\n236: | python-lint.yml | 3.10 |\n237: | codespell.yml | (system) |\n238: \n239: ### E2E Test Infrastructure\n240: \n241: **Kind Cluster:**\n242: - Name: `agentcube-e2e`\n243: - Kind version: v0.30.0\n244: - Created by: `kind create cluster` in `run_e2e.sh`\n245: \n246: **CRD Installation:**\n247: - Downloads agent-sandbox v0.1.1 by default\n248: - Applies manifest.yaml and extensions.yaml\n249: \n250: **Images Pre-loaded:**\n251: - `workloadmanager:latest` (built locally)\n252: - `agentcube-router:latest` (built locally)\n253: - `picod:latest` (built locally)\n254: - `redis:7-alpine` (pulled)\n255: - `python:3.9-slim` (pulled)\n256: \n257: **Port Forwards:**\n258: - Workload Manager: 8080 â†’ service/workloadmanager:8080\n259: - Router: 8081 â†’ service/agentcube-router:8080\n260: \n261: ---\n262: \n263: ## Implementation Plan\n264: \n265: ### Phase 1: Core Build & Lint Workflows\n266: \n267: - [ ] Create `.github/workflows/main.yml` â€” Docker build verification\n268: - [ ] Create `.github/workflows/lint.yml` â€” Go lint with path filter\n269: - [ ] Create `.github/workflows/codegen-check.yml` â€” Code generation verification\n270: \n271: ### Phase 2: Testing Workflows\n272: \n273: - [ ] Create `.github/workflows/test-coverage.yml` â€” Go coverage tests\n274: - [ ] Create `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` â€” Kind-based E2E tests\n275: - [ ] Create `.github/workflows/python-sdk-tests.yml` â€” Python SDK tests\n276: - [ ] Create `.github/workflows/python-lint.yml` â€” Ruff Python lint\n277: \n278: ### Phase 3: Quality Enforcement Workflows\n279: \n280: - [ ] Create `.github/workflows/codespell.yml` â€” Spelling checks\n281: - [ ] Create `.github/workflows/copyright-check.yml` â€” Header enforcement\n282: \n283: ### Phase 4: Release & Automation Workflows\n284: \n285: - [ ] Create `.github/workflows/build-push-release.yml` â€” Image publishing\n286: - [ ] Create `.github/workflows/dify-plugin-publish.yml` â€” Plugin release\n287: - [ ] Create `.github/workflows/workflows-approve.yml` â€” Contributor approval\n288: \n289: ### Phase 5: Integration\n290: \n291: - [ ] Add workflow dispatch for manual runs\n292: - [ ] Configure required status checks\n293: - [ ] Verify path filtering works correctly\n294: \n295: ---\n296: \n297: ## Acceptance Criteria\n298: \n299: | ID | Scenario | Expected Result |\n300: |----|----------|-----------------|\n301: | CI-001 | PR to main with Go changes | lint.yml and test-coverage.yml run |\n302: | CI-002 | PR to main with Python changes | python-lint.yml and python-sdk-tests.yml run |\n303: | CI-003 | PR with no relevant changes | No workflows trigger (path filter) |\n304: | CI-004 | Push to main branch | main.yml builds Docker image |\n305: | CI-005 | Tag push v1.0.0 | build-push-release.yml publishes images with tag v1.0.0 |\n306: | CI-006 | E2E workflow failure | Logs collected in e2e-logs artifact |\n307: | CI-007 | Codegen drift detected | Workflow fails with exit code |\n308: | CI-008 | Missing copyright header | copyright-check.yml fails |\n309: | CI-009 | Typo in code | codespell.yml fails |\n310: | CI-010 | First-time contributor PR | workflows-approve.yml queues for approval |\n311: | CI-011 | Dify plugin tag push | dify-plugin-publish.yml creates PR |\n312: | CI-012 | Workflow call from external | test-coverage.yml runs with optional token |\n313: \n314: ---\n315: \n316: ## Timeline Estimate\n317: \n318: | Phase | Workflows | Effort |\n319: |-------|-----------|--------|\n320: | Phase 1: Core Build & Lint | main, lint, codegen-check | 4 hours |\n321: | Phase 2: Testing | test-coverage, e2e, python-sdk-tests, python-lint | 6 hours |\n322: | Phase 3: Quality Enforcement | codespell, copyright-check | 2 hours |\n323: | Phase 4: Release & Automation | build-push-release, dify-plugin-publish, workflows-approve | 4 hours |\n324: | Phase 5: Integration | Testing, documentation | 2 hours |\n325: | **Total** | **12 workflows** | **18 hours** |\n326: \n327: ---\n328: \n329: ## Relationship to Other ARs\n330: \n331: This AR (AR-034) provides the CI/CD infrastructure that supports all other AgentCube implementation ARs:\n332: \n333: - **AR-029** (SDK HTTP Client) â€” Verified by python-sdk-tests.yml\n334: - **Future ARs** â€” Will use these workflows for validation\n335: \n336: The CI/CD infrastructure is foundationalâ€”without it, other ARs cannot be properly validated before merging.\n\n(End of file - total 336 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-034: CI/CD GitHub Actions\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement comprehensive GitHub Actions CI/CD infrastructure for the AgentCube project, consisting of 12 automated workflows covering build verification, linting, testing, code generation, end-to-end testing, release automation, and contributor workflow approvals.\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nThe AgentCube project requires robust CI/CD automation to ensure code quality, catch regressions early, and automate release processes. The project consists of multiple components:\n\n- **Go-based Workload Manager** (`workload-manager`)\n- **Go-based AgentD Controller** (`agentd`)\n- **Python SDK** (`sdk-python`)\n- **Kubernetes manifests and Helm charts**\n\nThe current manual build and test processes need automation through GitHub Actions to support:\n1. Pull request validation on multiple code paths\n2. Multi-architecture Docker image building and publishing","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775876799369,"end":1775876799385}}}}
