{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775876827165,"sessionID":"ses_2857ec447ffeq08FwzYRVyueq8","part":{"id":"prt_d7a81e81c001ddxQOqqA03aF2S","messageID":"msg_d7a81e270001M39PYZzfSnztcW","sessionID":"ses_2857ec447ffeq08FwzYRVyueq8","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876867145,"sessionID":"ses_2857ec447ffeq08FwzYRVyueq8","part":{"id":"prt_d7a81ea5c001uhLiQwxVq047kg","messageID":"msg_d7a81e270001M39PYZzfSnztcW","sessionID":"ses_2857ec447ffeq08FwzYRVyueq8","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_f2789cafcce64f1f910c2a6b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-034: CI/CD GitHub Actions â€” Technical Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Attribute | Value |\n|-----------|-------|\n| **Module** | `.github` |\n| **Language** | YAML (GitHub Actions) |\n| **Size** | L (12 workflows) |\n| **Stage** | ST-1 completed (Implementation ready) |\n| **Reference** | `ci-cd/design.md` (workflows reference) |\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### 1. Workflow Organization\n\n```\n.github/workflows/\nâ”śâ”€â”€ main.yml                    # Docker build on PR\nâ”śâ”€â”€ lint.yml                    # Go lint (golangci-lint)\nâ”śâ”€â”€ codegen-check.yml           # Code generation drift check\nâ”śâ”€â”€ test-coverage.yml           # Go test with coverage\nâ”śâ”€â”€ e2e.yml                     # End-to-end tests on Kind\nâ”śâ”€â”€ python-sdk-tests.yml        # Python SDK unit tests\nâ”śâ”€â”€ python-lint.yml             # Python Ruff linting\nâ”śâ”€â”€ codespell.yml               # Spelling verification\nâ”śâ”€â”€ copyright-check.yml         # Copyright header enforcement\nâ”śâ”€â”€ build-push-release.yml      # Release image publishing\nâ”śâ”€â”€ dify-plugin-publish.yml    # Dify plugin release automation\nâ””â”€â”€ workflows-approve.yml       # First-time contributor approval\n```\n\n### 2. Trigger Architecture\n\n| Trigger Type | Branches/Tags | Purpose |\n|--------------|---------------|---------|\n| `pull_request` | `main`, `release-*` | PR validation |\n| `push` | `main`, `v*.*.*`, `v*.*.*-*` | Main build + release tags |\n| `push` | `dify-plugin/v*` | Plugin publishing |\n| `merge_group` | â€” | Merge queue validation |\n| `workflow_call` | â€” | Reusable workflow invocation |\n| `pull_request_target` | `main`, `release-**` | Contributor approval |\n| `workflow_dispatch` | â€” | Manual trigger (future) |\n\n### 3. Path Filter Strategy\n\nUses `dorny/paths-filter` v2 for efficient conditional execution:\n\n| Filter Name | Patterns | Workflows |\n|-------------|----------|-----------|\n| `lint` | `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml` | lint.yml |\n| `codegen` | `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile` | codegen-check.yml |\n| `coverage` | `**` minus `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**` | test-coverage.yml |\n| `copyright` | All except `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**` | copyright-check.yml |\n| `python` | `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml` | python-lint.yml |\n| `sdk` | `sdk-python/**` | python-sdk-tests.yml |\n\n### 4. Runner Matrix\n\n| Language | Version | Workflows |\n|----------|---------|-----------|\n| Go | 1.24 | lint.yml, test-coverage.yml |\n| Go | 1.24.4 | codegen-check.yml, build-push-release.yml |\n| Go | 1.23 | e2e.yml |\n| Python | 3.12 | python-sdk-tests.yml |\n| Python | 3.10 | python-lint.yml |\n\n---\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### 1. Workflow Metadata\n\n```yaml\n# Example: Workflow structure template\nname: <workflow-name>\non:\n  pull_request:\n    branches: [main, 'release-*']\n  push:\n    branches: [main]\n\nconcurrency:\n  group: ${{ github.workflow }}-${{ github.ref }}\n  cancel-in-progress: true\n```\n\n### 2. Job Configuration\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  <job-name>:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - name: Checkout\n        uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      \n      - name: Path Filter\n        if: <conditional>\n        uses: dorny/paths-filter@v2\n        id: filter\n        with:\n          filters: |\n            <filter-name>:\n              - '<pattern>'\n      \n      - name: Run Action\n        if: steps.filter.outputs.<filter-name> == 'true'\n        run: |\n          <command>\n```\n\n### 3. Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Scope | Description |\n|----------|-------|-------------|\n| `ARTIFACTS_PATH` | E2E workflow | Log collection directory |\n| `TAG` | Release workflow | Image tag (from git ref) |\n| `IMAGE_REGISTRY` | Release workflow | Container registry URL |\n| `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | E2E test | Workload Manager endpoint |\n| `ROUTER_URL` | E2E test | Router endpoint |\n| `API_TOKEN` | E2E test | Kubernetes service account token |\n\n### 4. Secrets\n\n| Secret | Workflows | Purpose |\n|--------|-----------|---------|\n| `GITHUB_TOKEN` | build-push-release, workflows-approve | GHCR login, API operations |\n| `CODECOV_TOKEN` | test-coverage | Coverage upload (optional) |\n| `GH_TOKEN` | dify-plugin-publish | Cross-repo PR creation |\n\n---\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### 1. Workflow Dispatch Inputs\n\n```yaml\n# Future: Manual workflow trigger\non:\n  workflow_dispatch:\n    inputs:\n      test-suite:\n        type: choice\n        options: [unit, integration, e2e]\n        required: true\n      go-version:\n        type: string\n        default: '1.24'\n```\n\n### 2. Workflow Call Inputs/Outputs\n\n```yaml\n# test-coverage.yml reusable workflow\non:\n  workflow_call:\n    inputs:\n      go-version:\n        type: string\n        default: '1.24'\n    secrets:\n      codecov-token:\n        required: false\n    outputs:\n      coverage-passed:\n        description: \"Whether coverage threshold met\"\n        value: ${{ jobs.coverage.outputs.coverage-passed }}\n```\n\n### 3. Job Outputs\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  coverage:\n    outputs:\n      coverage-passed: ${{ steps.coverage-check.outputs.passed }}\n    steps:\n      - id: coverage-check\n        run: |\n          PASSED=$((${{ steps.coverage.outputs.coverage }} >= 80))\n          echo \"passed=$PASSED\" >> $GITHUB_OUTPUT\n```\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### 1. Step-Level Error Handling\n\n```yaml\n- name: Build Docker image\n  run: make docker-build\n  continue-on-error: false  # Fail workflow on error\n\n- name: Optional coverage upload\n  if: success() && steps.codecov.outputs.token\n  run: codecov/upload-action@...\n```\n\n### 2. Job-Level Failure Handling\n\n```yaml\n- name: Collect logs on failure\n  if: failure()\n  run: |\n    ./scripts/collect-logs.sh\n  \n- name: Cleanup always\n  if: always()\n  run: make e2e-clean\n```\n\n### 3. Retry and Timeout\n\n```yaml\n- name: Unstable test\n  uses: nick-fields/retry@v3\n  with:\n    timeout_minutes: 10\n    max_attempts: 3\n    command: go test -v ./test/e2e/...\n```\n\n### 4. Error Conditions\n\n| Condition | Handling | Workflow |\n|-----------|----------|----------|\n| Docker build failure | Fail fast | main.yml |\n| Lint errors | Fail with output | lint.yml |\n| Coverage below threshold | Warn only (optional) | test-coverage.yml |\n| E2E test failure | Upload artifacts, fail | e2e.yml |\n| Codegen drift | Fail with diff | codegen-check.yml |\n| Kind cluster creation | Fail with logs | e2e.yml |\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### 1. Workflow Validation\n\n#### Syntax Validation\n```bash\n# Validate workflow YAML syntax\nactionlint .github/workflows/*.yml\n\n# Alternative: yamllint\nyamllint -c .yamllint .github/workflows/\n```\n\n#### Dry-Run Testing\n```bash\n# Use act (GitHub Actions local runner) for testing\nact -l  # List workflows\nact -n  # Dry-run\n```\n\n### 2. Path Filter Testing\n\n```bash\n# Verify path filters match expected files\n# Test: Modify a Go file, verify lint.yml triggers but python-lint.yml doesn't\ngit checkout main\necho \"// test\" >> pkg/test.go\ngit diff --name-only  # Should show pkg/test.go\n```\n\n### 3. Integration Testing\n\n| Test | Method | Verification |\n|------|--------|--------------|\n| Docker build | Run main.yml locally | Image created |\n| Lint check | Run on modified code | Lint errors detected |\n| E2E on Kind | Execute e2e.yml | Cluster created, tests pass |\n| Path filter | Modify filtered paths | Correct workflow triggers |\n| Release build | Tag push simulation | Images pushed to GHCR |\n\n### 4. Test Coverage for Workflows\n\n```yaml\n# Example: Workflow that tests other workflows\nname: Workflow Integration Test\non:\n  pull_request:\n    paths:\n      - '.github/workflows/**'\n\njobs:\n  validate-workflows:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      - name: Validate YAML\n        run: |\n          for f in .github/workflows/*.yml; do\n            python3 -c \"import yaml; yaml.safe_load(open('$f'))\" || exit 1\n          done\n      - name: Check action versions\n        run: |\n          grep -h 'uses:' .github/workflows/*.yml | sort -u\n```\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Core Workflows\n- [ ] `main.yml` â€” Docker build verification\n- [ ] `lint.yml` â€” Go lint with path filter\n\n### Phase 2: Testing Workflows\n- [ ] `test-coverage.yml` â€” Go coverage with codecov\n- [ ] `e2e.yml` â€” Kind cluster E2E tests\n- [ ] `codegen-check.yml` â€” Code generation verification\n\n### Phase 3: Python Workflows\n- [ ] `python-sdk-tests.yml` â€” Python SDK tests\n- [ ] `python-lint.yml` â€” Python Ruff linting\n\n### Phase 4: Quality Workflows\n- [ ] `codespell.yml` â€” Spelling checks\n- [ ] `copyright-check.yml` â€” Header enforcement\n\n### Phase 5: Release Workflows\n- [ ] `build-push-release.yml` â€” Image publishing\n- [ ] `dify-plugin-publish.yml` â€” Plugin release\n- [ ] `workflows-approve.yml` â€” Contributor approval\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Action | Version | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|---------|\n| `actions/checkout` | v4 | Repository checkout |\n| `actions/setup-go` | v5 | Go environment |\n| `actions/setup-python` | v5 | Python environment |\n| `docker/setup-buildx-action` | v3 | Docker buildx |\n| `docker/login-action` | v3 | GHCR login |\n| `dorny/paths-filter` | v2 | Path-based filtering |\n| `helm/kind-action` | v1 | Kind cluster |\n| `codecov/codecov-action` | v4 | Coverage upload |\n| `aws-actions/configure-aws-credentials` | v4 | AWS (future) |\n\n---\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n1. **Secret Management**: Use GitHub Secrets for all sensitive data\n2. **Token Scoping**: Use minimal token scopes for workflow permissions\n3. **Path Filtering**: Prevent unnecessary workflow runs\n4. **Concurrency**: Cancel in-progress runs on new pushes\n5. **Artifact Handling**: Clean up artifacts after retention period\n6. **External Actions**: Pin to specific versions (SHA preferred)\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Proposal: `proposal.md` (AR-034)\n- Specification: `ci-cd/spec.md`\n- Workflow Reference: `ci-cd/design.md`\n- Makefile: `Makefile` (build targets)\n- E2E Setup: `test/e2e/run_e2e.sh`","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/.github/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/.github/design.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/.github/design.md","time":{"start":1775876867134,"end":1775876867143}}}}
